-- South African Coal Has Longest Losing Streak in Four Months
-- B y   M a r e k   S t r z e l e c k i
-- 2012-03-19T11:42:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-19/south-african-coal-has-longest-losing-streak-in-four-months.html
Coal export prices at  South
Africa ’s  Richards Bay , the continent’s biggest terminal for
shipping the fuel, declined for the third week, the longest
losing streak in four months.  Prices (CLSPSARB)  dropped 80 cents, or 0.8 percent, to $103.05 a
metric ton in the week ended March 16, the least since Dec. 16,
according to IHS McCloskey data on Bloomberg. That’s the lowest
level since Dec. 16.  The price is quoted on a free-on-board basis, which
excludes delivery costs.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marek Strzelecki in Warsaw at 
 mstrzelecki1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Lars Paulsson in London at 
 lpaulsson@bloomberg.net  